Package org.tquadrat.foundation.javadoc

Class AuthorTaglet

java.lang.Object
org.tquadrat.foundation.javadoc.AuthorTaglet
All Implemented Interfaces:
Taglet
@ClassVersion(sourceVersion="$Id: AuthorTaglet.java 977 2022-01-06 11:41:03Z tquadrat $") @API(status=STABLE, since="0.0.5") public final class AuthorTaglet extends Object implements Taglet

This taglet replaces the standard @author taglet. It is different in the way that it provides the author's email address as a hyperlink.

This means that the tag requires the reference to the author in the format below:

  @extauthor <name> - <email address>

Basically, this is the name of the author, followed by their email address, separated by a hyphen ("-" or &#x2d;), surrounded by blanks.

If there is no email address, the output is the same as for the standard @author taglet.

Previously (before Java 15), it was possible to "overwrite" the default @author tag by a custom implementation. Unfortunately, this does not work any longer: when providing a custom tag with the same name, no author is added to the output at all.
